It’s not easy for a child to communicate their needs especially if it’s in regards to being socially anxious and they are socially anxious🤝 All is forgiven but I just wanted to share bc my sister found a CLASSY Ladies T-Shirt at Goodwill and it triggered this memory.

Every time I looked at the stuffed animal they gave us, I would get war flashbacks. I had to get rid of it. This entire situation was preventable. I could have gone and had a good time if the hosts would have done their part in making sure the kids were comfortable but I digress.

I didn’t know what sex was at the time so a lot of it went over my head but when they started taking about puberty I got super freaked out for some reason😭 I just remember being SO uncomfortable. It was just so much for one night y’all. I was still recovering from the dance off

This was more my style since I’m super big on all things art so I was thriving for a brief moment until we went to the science room where they thought it would be a great time educate us on sex Ed and puberty and things.

I had a full blown anxiety attack and was sitting there with my head in my hands hiding my tears from the other girls. When people asked me what was wrong I just said I was tired bc I was embarrassed. At some point in the night we went to a room and made Christmas ornaments

I was in the corner of the gym shuffling around while 40-50 y/o women and a few 8th graders were shouting “cmon dance!!!” At me until finally one of the 8th graders tapped me on the shoulder and put me out of my misery.

..and she kept saying “cmon everyone is dancing it’s fun!” And just ignoring the fact that I was visibly uncomfortable. The rules of the dance off were that we all are spaced out and dance and then the judges gradually tap people to be thrown out of the competition.

And I did but it was intense negative emotions. So here’s the juicy details. There was a dance off competition with a dj in the gym and I suffered from intense social anxiety at the time and dancing was NOT something I would ever do. I told one of the hosts I didn’t want to...

At the lock-in there was food which was nice of them. We were all given a stuffed animal and it was a big deal lol a CLASSY Ladies tradition or something idk. The 8th grader there acted like her stuffed animal greatly impacted her life so I was expecting to feel something

The initial meetings weren’t too crazy we would have a snack and talk about random stuff I guess. I don’t remember a lot from those but what I do remember is the lock-in. A core traumatic middle school memory for me.

I’ll take us back to the beginning. I was pulled out of my science class with two other girls and we were given an orange slip of paper inviting us to be in the club. I took it home and my mom insisted that I go. I was iffy but I was feeling optimistic so I went.

Thinking about this club I was randomly selected (?) for in 6th grade. It was called “CLASSY Ladies.” It was all girls and we met every other week for an activity. Keep reading my thread for traumatic memories 😝
